# Code Conventions

## Component Structure

All site sections live as **named function components** directly in `src/app/page.tsx`. There is no separate `components/` folder for page sections — keep it that way unless a component is genuinely reusable across pages.

```
page.tsx sections (in render order):
  Hero → Episodes → About → GuestVerticals → CTABanner → Footer
```

Shared/reusable components go in `src/components/`. Currently:
- `XPostEmbed.tsx` — client component for Twitter/X post embeds
- `XTimelineEmbed.tsx` — client component for Twitter/X timeline embeds

## Naming

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Page section functions | PascalCase | `function Episodes()` |
| Inline SVG icon components | PascalCase + "Icon" suffix | `function XIcon(...)` |
| CSS custom classes | kebab-case | `.section-px`, `.animate-fade-up` |
| Config keys | camelCase | `xProfileUrl`, `youtubeUrl`, `guestTitle` |
| File names | kebab-case | `XPostEmbed.tsx`, `globals.css` |

## Tailwind CSS v4

This project uses **Tailwind v4** (PostCSS plugin, not the traditional `tailwind.config.js`). Design tokens are defined in `globals.css` under `@theme inline {}`:

```css
@theme inline {
  --color-background: #ffffff;
  --color-foreground: #000000;
  --color-inverse-bg: #0a0a0a;
  --color-inverse-fg: #ffffff;
  --color-muted: #737373;
  --color-border: #e5e5e5;
  --font-sans: var(--font-geist);
  --font-display: var(--font-special-gothic);
}
```

Use these semantic tokens in Tailwind classes:
- `bg-background` / `text-foreground` — light sections
- `bg-inverse-bg` / `text-inverse-fg` — dark sections (Hero, CTABanner, Footer)
- `text-muted` — secondary/caption text
- `border-border` — standard border color
- `font-sans` — body text (Geist)
- `font-display` — headings (Special Gothic Expanded One, always uppercase)

## Section Layout Pattern

Every section follows this structure:

```tsx
<section className="bg-background text-foreground section-px section-py">
  <div className="w-full max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    {/* content */}
  </div>
</section>
```

- `.section-px` — responsive horizontal padding (1.5rem → 2.5rem → 4rem)
- `.section-py` — responsive vertical padding (5rem → 6rem → 8rem)
- Max content width is `max-w-2xl` (42rem) for most sections, `max-w-3xl` for Hero

## Animation Classes

Defined in `globals.css`. Use on entrance elements:

| Class | Effect |
|-------|--------|
| `.animate-fade-up` | Fade in from below |
| `.animate-fade-in` | Fade in (no movement) |
| `.animate-slide-in-left` | Slide in from left |
| `.delay-1` to `.delay-5` | Stagger delays (0.1s to 0.7s) |

## Responsive Breakpoints

Mobile-first. Breakpoints used:
- `sm:` — 640px (tablet portrait)
- `lg:` — 1024px (desktop)
- `xl:` — 1280px (wide desktop)

Pattern: `text-xs sm:text-sm`, `py-5 sm:py-7`, `hidden sm:block`

## Inline SVG Icons

All icons are defined at the top of `page.tsx` as small functional components with a `size` prop:

```tsx
function XIcon({ size = 18 }: { size?: number }) {
  return (
    <svg width={size} height={size} viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
      {/* path */}
    </svg>
  );
}
```

Icons in use: `XIcon`, `YouTubeIcon`, `CalendarIcon`, `ArrowIcon`, `PlayIcon`.

To add a new icon: define it the same way at the top of the file, before the first section function.

## Typography

Headings (`h1`, `h2`, `h3`) use Special Gothic — set globally in `globals.css` — always `uppercase`, `letter-spacing: -0.02em`. Don't override these per-element unless necessary.

Body and UI text use Geist via `font-sans`. Common patterns:
```
font-sans text-xs tracking-widest uppercase   → labels/badges
font-sans text-sm text-muted                  → captions
font-sans text-base font-medium               → list items
font-sans text-[10px]                         → tiny metadata
```

## Fonts

Loaded in `layout.tsx` via `next/font/google`:
- `Geist` → CSS variable `--font-geist` → used as `font-sans`
- `Special_Gothic_Expanded_One` (weight 400) → CSS variable `--font-special-gothic` → used as `font-display`

## Buttons & Interactive Elements

Primary button pattern:
```tsx
className="group inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 bg-white !text-[#000000] font-sans font-medium text-sm px-8 py-4 transition-all duration-300 hover:bg-white/90 active:scale-[0.97] touch-manipulation"
```

Platform pill badge pattern:
```tsx
className="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-sans text-[10px] border border-border rounded-full px-2.5 py-1 text-muted hover:text-foreground hover:border-foreground transition-colors"
```

Always include `touch-manipulation` on tap targets for mobile responsiveness.

## TypeScript

Strict mode is on. Config values are inferred from `siteConfig` — no explicit interface needed unless the type is used across files. Optional fields use `?` (e.g. `xUrl?`, `youtubeUrl?`).

Path alias: `@/*` maps to `src/*`. Use it for imports across directories.
